@description TotalReaper
@author Frank Acklin
@version 0.1.4
@changelog
  Use REAPERAPI_MINIMAL so the plugin loads on REAPER older than the SDK pin
  Static-link the MSVC runtime on Windows (no VC++ Redistributable required)
  Pin macOS deployment target to 11.0 (Big Sur) for arm64 + older Intel coverage
  Fix stereo monitoring: skip balpan on stereo inputs, enforce B_MAINSEND every tick
@provides
  [darwin-arm64] reaper_totalreaper-arm64.dylib https://github.com/acklin83/totalreaper/releases/download/v$version/$path
  [win64] reaper_totalreaper.dll https://github.com/acklin83/totalreaper/releases/download/v$version/$path
@link
  GitHub https://github.com/acklin83/totalreaper
  Issue tracker https://github.com/acklin83/totalreaper/issues
@about
  # TotalReaper

  REAPER ↔ RME TotalMix FX Global OSC bridge. Turns RME interfaces (UFX+ family) into a fully DAW-controlled hardware console — mic gain, 48V phantom, pad, phase, submix sends, all driven from REAPER tracks via TotalMix FX 2.1's Global OSC protocol.

  *In Erinnerung an ASIO Direct Monitoring in Samplitude.*

  ## What it does

  - **Routing mirror**: REAPER track volume / mute / pan → TotalMix input matrix in real time. REAPER's software monitor is muted while the mirror is engaged so you only hear TotalMix's hardware (zero-latency) path.
  - **Track-to-track sends** are walked recursively and projected onto TotalMix routings on every hardware-output destination — cue mixes, headphone sends, etc.
  - **Per-track preamp control** as REAPER actions: gain ±1 dB, 48V toggle, pad toggle (with mute pulse to hide the hardware pop), phase invert. Multi-select.
  - **Stereo input handling**: stereo-linked TotalMix pairs and 2-mono splits both work correctly — TotalMix's own balance handling is preserved.

  ## Requirements

  - REAPER 6 or later (tested through 7.71)
  - TotalMix FX 2.1 Alpha 4 or later, with Global OSC enabled (Settings → OSC → Compatibility Mode → Global OSC)
  - RME interface that supports Global OSC (UFX+, UCX II, etc.)

  ## Out of scope

  TotalMix-internal effects (channel EQ, dynamics, room EQ, FX send/return) — those stay in TotalMix.

  ## After install

  Find all actions in REAPER's Action List by typing "TotalReaper". Run **TotalReaper: Toggle Routing Mirror** to engage.
